{"type":"message","id":"9dd7ae05","parentId":"5b0d5c1d","timestamp":"2026-02-17T19:10:03.460Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Reviewing Edit Indentation**\n\nI'm now zeroing in on the correct indentation for the edit. I remember writing the file, so I know the content. I'll make sure to get the indentation exactly right, referencing the `scripts/exec_guard.py` file to avoid any mistakes this time. It's a simple fix, but getting it right is crucial.\n\n\n**Revisiting Indentation Strategy**\n\nI'm verifying my previous assumption about the edit's indentation. I'm focusing on the `scripts/exec_guard.py` file, as I recall writing the content there before. The key here is to determine whether the problem lies with my original write or in the contextual lines surrounding it.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771355403452_93","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"scripts/exec_guard.py"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":10196,"output":133,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":10329,"cost":{"input":0.020392,"output":0.001596,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.021988}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771355394414}}
{"type":"message","id":"404198de","parentId":"9dd7ae05","timestamp":"2026-02-17T19:10:03.478Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"read_1771355403452_93","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import sys\nimport subprocess\nimport os\n\ndef run_guarded_command(command):\n    \"\"\"\n    Executes a command, captures output, implements pagination, and logs full output.\n    \"\"\"\n    # Ensure logs directory exists\n    os.makedirs(\"logs\", exist_ok=True)\n    log_file = \"logs/last_exec.log\"\n\n    try:\n        # Run command and capture output\n        # Use shell=True for flexibility.\n        # Force encoding to utf-8 to avoid charmap errors on Windows, or use errors='replace'\n        # Env vars might be needed for encoding\n        env = os.environ.copy()\n        env[\"PYTHONIOENCODING\"] = \"utf-8\"\n        \n        result = subprocess.run(\n            command, \n            shell=True, \n            capture_output=True, \n            text=True, \n            encoding='utf-8', \n            errors='replace',\n            env=env\n        )\n        \n        stdout = result.stdout if result.stdout else \"\"\n        stderr = result.stderr if result.stderr else \"\"\n        \n        full_output = stdout\n        if stderr:\n            full_output += \"\\n[STDERR]\\n\" + stderr\n\n        # Log full output\n        with open(log_file, \"w\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n            f.write(full_output)\n\n        lines = stdout.splitlines()\n        line_count = len(lines)\n        \n        # Pagination Logic\n        if line_count > 20:\n            head = lines[:10]\n            tail = lines[-10:]\n            \n            print(\"\\n\".join(head))\n            print(f\"\\n... [{line_count - 20} lines hidden. See {log_file}] ...\\n\")\n            print(\"\\n\".join(tail))\n        else:\n            print(stdout)\n            \n        if stderr:\n            print(\"[STDERR]\", stderr)\n\n    except Exception as e:\n        print(f\"Error executing command: {e}\")\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    if len(sys.argv) < 2:\n        print(\"Usage: python exec_guard.py <command>\")\n    else:\n        # Reconstruct command from args\n        cmd = \" \".join(sys.argv[1:])\n        \n        # Import os_utils to sanitize/translate\n        try:\n            # Add src to path\n            current_dir = os.path.dirname(os.path.abspath(__file__))\n            src_path = os.path.abspath(os.path.join(current_dir, \"../src\"))\n            sys.path.append(src_path)\n            \n            from core.os_utils import get_safe_command\n            cmd = get_safe_command(cmd)\n            # print(f\"DEBUG: Executing safe command: {cmd}\") \n        except ImportError:\n            print(\"Warning: Could not import os_utils. Running raw command.\")\n            \n        run_guarded_command(cmd)\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771355403476}}
{"type":"message","id":"1a0efabf","parentId":"404198de","timestamp":"2026-02-17T19:11:25.432Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Contemplating Code Edits**\n\nI'm zeroing in on the script modifications. The core edit involves using `powershell.exe` in `scripts/exec_guard.py` on Windows. I'm focusing on preserving the original code's indentation, especially the nested structure within the `try:` block. I'm scrutinizing the file to ensure the formatting matches precisely.\n\n\n**Confirming Execution Strategy**\n\nI'm now fully committed to rewriting `scripts/exec_guard.py` using a complete write operation to eliminate any formatting errors. This approach allows me to definitively address the executable issue on Windows by specifying `powershell.exe` directly. I will also be verifying that the `get_safe_command` logic functions as intended following this change. I'm satisfied that `src/core/os_utils.py` does indeed handle the correct replacement.\n\n\n**Solidifying Implementation Plan**\n\nI'm now completely settled on the course of action. I'll rewrite `scripts/exec_guard.py` to specify `powershell.exe` on Windows, confirming the overall structure with a complete write for accuracy. I'm also going to rewrite `src/core/os_utils.py` to guarantee the `&&` replacement. This approach provides assurance regarding the functionality of `get_safe_command` and PowerShell compatibility, especially for versions prior to 7.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"write_1771355485307_94","name":"write","arguments":{"file_path":"src/core/os_utils.py","content":"import os\n\ndef get_safe_command(cmd: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"\n    Translates common shell commands to be safe and compatible with the current OS.\n    Currently focuses on adapting Linux-style commands for Windows PowerShell.\n    \"\"\"\n    if os.name != 'nt':\n        return cmd\n\n    # Basic translation for Windows PowerShell\n    \n    # Replace && with ; (PowerShell 5.1 uses ; as separator)\n    # We replace \" && \" with \" ; \" to handle chaining.\n    safe_cmd = cmd.replace(\" && \", \" ; \")\n\n    # Replace rm -rf with Remove-Item -Recurse -Force\n    if \"rm -rf \" in safe_cmd:\n        safe_cmd = safe_cmd.replace(\"rm -rf \", \"Remove-Item -Recurse -Force \")\n    elif safe_cmd.strip() == \"rm -rf\":\n        safe_cmd = \"Remove-Item -Recurse -Force\"\n    \n    return safe_cmd\n"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":11057,"output":1013,"cacheRead":8416,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":12070,"cost":{"input":0.022113999999999998,"output":0.012156,"cacheRead":0.0016832000000000001,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0359532}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771355403478}}
